main event: A light reflection was observed in Alexandria, Virginia on August 2, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for only a few seconds.
The object was described as a round light with hazy edges, about the size of 10 falling stars, and yellowish-white in color.
No sound was associated with the object.
The observation was evaluated as a reflection of light on a windshield.
The report concluded that there was insufficient information to make a definitive determination.
